1. Explain in detail about Agile Methodology given simple explain
  Introduction
    Agile Methodology is a modern approach to software development and project management.
    It focuses on completing work in small parts, delivering results quickly, and making improvements based on customer feedback.
   
  Definition
    Agile is a methodology that helps teams develop products through continuous planning, development, testing, and feedback.
    It allows changes to be made easily during the project.
    
  Simple Definition:
    Agile is a flexible method of developing a project in small stages while regularly getting customer feedback.
    
  Why Agile is Needed
    Traditional development methods take a long time to deliver the final product.
    If customer requirements change, it becomes difficult and costly to make modifications.
    
  Agile solves this problem by:
    Delivering work faster.
    Allowing changes at any stage.
    Improving communication.
    Increasing customer satisfaction.
    
  Key Features of Agile
    1. Incremental Development
       The project is divided into small parts called iterations or sprints.
    2. Customer Involvement
       Customers provide feedback regularly during development.
    3. Flexibility
       Requirements can be changed even during the project.
    4. Team Collaboration
       Developers, testers, and customers work together.
    5. Continuous Testing
       Testing is done throughout the project instead of only at the end.
       
  Agile Life Cycle
    1. Requirement Gathering
       Collect customer needs.
       Understand project goals.
    2. Planning
       Create a plan for the work.
       Prioritize important features.
    3. Design
       Design the system or application.
    4. Development
       Develop features in small modules.
    5. Testing
       Test each module to find and fix errors.
    6. Review
       Show the completed work to the customer.
       Collect feedback.
    7. Release
       Deliver the product to users.
    8. Maintenance
       Fix bugs and add improvements.
       
  Agile Process
       Create a list of requirements (Product Backlog).
       Select tasks for a sprint.
       Develop and test the selected features.
       Deliver a working product.
       Get customer feedback.
       Improve the product in the next sprint
       
  Agile Team Roles
     Product Owner
       Represents the customer.
       Decides project requirements.
       Prioritizes tasks.
     Scrum Master
       Guides the Agile process.
       Removes obstacles for the team
     Development Team
       Developers, testers, and designers.
       Build and test the product.
       
   Advantages of Agile
       Faster Delivery
       Products are delivered in small parts quickly.
       Better Quality
       Continuous testing improves quality.
       Customer Satisfaction
       Customers can see progress and provide feedback.
       Easy to Handle Changes
       Requirements can be modified at any time.
       Reduced Risk
       Problems are identified early.
       Better Team Communication
       Frequent meetings improve collaboration.

  Disadvantages of Agile
       Requires Customer Participation
       Customers must be involved regularly.
       Less Documentation
       Documentation may be limited.
       Difficult Cost Estimation
      Project scope can change frequently.
      Team Dependency

      
2. Explain about Monitoring Activity given simple expline
   Introduction
      Monitoring Activity is the process of regularly checking and tracking the progress of a project to ensure that it is moving according to the plan.
     It helps managers identify problems early and take corrective actions before they become serious.

   Simple Definition:
     Monitoring is the continuous observation and measurement of project activities to ensure that goals are achieved on time, within budget, and with the required quality.

   Purpose of Monitoring
     Track project progress.
     Compare actual work with planned work.
     Identify problems and risks early.
     Ensure resources are used properly.
     Improve project performance.
     Help complete the project successfully.
     Importance of Monitoring

   Monitoring is important because it:
     Ensures the project stays on schedule.
     Helps control costs and budget.
     Improves the quality of work.
     Detects risks and issues early.
     Supports better decision-making.
     Increases the chances of project success.
 
  Types of Monitoring Activities
     1. Progress Monitoring
          Checks whether project tasks are completed as planned.
     Example:
          Tracking how many tasks have been completed in a week.
     2. Schedule Monitoring
          Ensures that work is progressing according to the project timeline.
     Example:
          Checking whether a task is completed before its deadline.
    3. Cost Monitoring
          Tracks project expenses and budget usage.
    Example:
          Comparing actual spending with the planned budget.
    4. Quality Monitoring
          Checks whether the work meets quality standards.
    Example:
          Testing software to find and fix errors.
    5. Risk Monitoring
          Identifies and evaluates possible risks during the project.
    Example:
          Monitoring delays caused by resource shortages.
    6. Resource Monitoring
          Tracks the use of people, equipment, and materials.
    Example:
          Checking team workload and productivity.

Monitoring Process
Step 1: Set Objectives
        Define what needs to be monitored.
Step 2: Collect Information
        Gather data about project activities.
Step 3: Compare Results
        Compare actual performance with planned performance.
Step 4: Identify Problems
        Find any delays, risks, or issues.
Step 5: Take Corrective Action
        Implement solutions to improve performance.
Step 6: Report Progress
        Share project status with stakeholders.

Monitoring Tools
  Progress reports
  Status meetings
  Dashboards
  Checklists
  Burndown charts (in Agile projects)
  Project management software

Benefits of Monitoring
   Better project control.
   Early problem detection.
   Improved quality.
   Efficient use of resources.
   Timely project completion.
   Increased customer satisfaction.
